h3. Issue Summary
Let's say we are exporting a meeting notes page tree to HTML. When we unzip the file, opening the meeting notes index page and try to click over one of the listed meeting note links, it will open a file not found window, though the file is there.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new page called *A*;
# Add the *Content Report Table*;
# In the macro settings, set the Label field with "_banana_" and let the current space set;
# Publish the page;
# Create a new page called *B* and let it under page *A*;
# Publish the page and add the label "_banana_" in it;
# Go to *Space Settings > Content Tools > Export* and perform a custom HTML export picking page *A* and *B*;
# After unzipping the exported file, open page *A* HTML file;
# Click in the link to page *B*.

h3. Expected Results
Page *B* file is opened in the browser.

h3. Actual Results
The *File Not Found* message appears.

*Notes*
* The link within the macro after exporting it to HTML is set this way: *{{file:///wiki/spaces/SPACE_KEY/pages/CONTENTID/PAGE_TITLE}}* instead of *{{file:///Users/USERNAME/Downloads/SPACE_KEY%204/PAGE_TITLE_CONTENTID.html}}*

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

