h3. Issue Summary
When we are working with third-party add-ons that allow us to create diagrams (such as Draw.io, Gliphy or Balsamiq), after inserting the created diagram on a Confluence page and publishing the page, a .PNG file is created and gets uploaded to the page. 

When we are creating a new page, if we go to *Files and Images* button, the .PNG files uploaded by the add-ons are not listed in the *Recent Uploads* list.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page;
# Call the macro of your favorite diagram add-on;
# Create and insert the diagram in the Confluence pages;
# Publish the page;
# Create a new page on Confluence;
# Click over the *Files & Images* button.

h3. Expected Results
The .PNG file is listed as a recent upload.

h3. Actual Results
The .PNG file from the add-on is not listed there.

h3. Workaround
You can download the first created .PNG file and manually upload it to the new Confluence page - then, if you create a new page where that file is still needed, it will be listed in the *Recent Uploads* list.
